As an introverted creative entrepreneur who values privacy, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to interact with large (evil) tech companies in an outgoing manner. Here, follow the algorithms, share your personality charm. Get verified on that service, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and reply immediately. Video, video, still video.
1/3
This year has been a year of transformation for me.
I no longer want to dedicate my money, data, and energy to large tech companies or listen to mentors who only offer one-size-fits-all outgoing solutions. I am exploring new business models while also working to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by doing things a certain way.
Fingers crossed for me!
Step one is done.
I exited Facebook, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also deleted the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, and felt great about it.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will be migrating my business over in the coming weeks.
I transferred my MX records to Proton, now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, and no longer have to pay Google for basic email validation.
3/3
