Website: Check out @user5. It looks easy to use and has a nice interface, and it's open-source. I plan to migrate one of my websites over before my next renewal.
Signal: Look at cal.com. This is an open-source calendar service that integrates scheduling for Element, JITSI, and other video calls. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested whether you can just send messages or make video calls yet.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open-source.
